}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Create a new item in a secret service collection and return its D-Bus
object path.</p>  <p>It is often easier to use <link xref="Secret.password_store_sync"/> or <link xref="Secret.Item.create_sync"/>
rather than using this function. Using this method requires that you setup
a correct hash table of D-Bus <code>properties</code> for the new collection.</p>  <p>If the <code>flags</code> contains <link xref="Secret.ItemCreateFlags"/>.replace, then the secret
service will search for an item matching the @attributes, and update that item
instead of creating a new one.</p>  <p><code>properties</code> is a set of properties for the new collection. The keys in the
hash table should be interface.property strings like
&lt;literal&gt;org.freedesktop.Secret.Item.Label&lt;/literal&gt;. The values
in the hash table should be <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link> values of the properties.</p>  <p>This method may block indefinitely and should not be used in user interface
threads. The secret service may prompt the user. <link xref="Secret.Service.prompt"/>
will be used to handle any prompts that are required.</p>

